am Lead",{"className":"rounded-full bg-tag-bg px-2.5 py-0.5 font-mono text-[11px] text-accent","children":"Team Lead"}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"mb-3 relative aspect-video w-full overflow-hidden rounded-[10px]","children":["$","$L3",null,{"src":"/images/baja/baja-cad.png","alt":"Full vehicle CAD assembly in Fusion 360, isometric view showing double A-arm suspension at all four corners","fill":true,"className":"object-cover","priority":true}]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"mb-16 font-mono text-[12px] text-muted","children":"Full vehicle assembly — Fusion 360"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"mb-16","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"mb-4 text-[20px] font-semibold text-primary","children":"What it is"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"space-y-4 text-[15px] leading-[1.75] text-secondary","children":[["$","p",null,{"children":"Davidson College's Baja SAE team is in its second year. We're building a single-seat off-road vehicle from scratch to compete against 100+ university teams in the SAE Baja series, a competition that includes a four-hour endurance race on rough terrain, hill climbs, and maneuverability events."}],["$","p",null,{"children":"I'm the primary engineer on a three-person leadership team. My job is to design virtually every component and get it built, either fabricating it myself or delegating to one of our 10+ members. The other two leads handle finances and club operations. Every engineering decision goes through me. Nothing gets finalized without sign-off from all three of us."}],["$","p",null,{"children":"We compete Spring 2026."}]]}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"mb-16","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"mb-4 text-[20px] font-semibold text-primary","children":"What we started with"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"space-y-6 text-[15px] leading-[1.75] text-secondary","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"relative aspect-[4/3] w-full overflow-hidden rounded-[10px]","children":["$","$L3",null,{"src":"/images/baja/baja-inherited.jpg","alt":"Bare welded chassis frame with two people examining it in the Lake Campus boathouse","fill":true,"className":"object-cover"}]}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Davidson's program is only in its second year. We inherited a partially welded chassis from last year's team and have been building everything else from scratch. No institutional knowledge to fall back on, no senior members who've done it before, no big budget."}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Low budget means we fabricate most of what we need ourselves. Every bracket, every mount, every suspension component has been designed in CAD, reviewed by the team, and either welded in the shop or sent to a local manufacturer for parts we can't make ourselves. We write the BOMs, get the quotes, and negotiate sponsorships to offset costs."}]]}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"mb-16","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"mb-4 text-[20px] font-semibold text-primary","children":"Suspension — my primary responsibility"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"space-y-6 text-[15px] leading-[1.75] text-secondary","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"relative aspect-[4/3] w-full overflow-hidden rounded-[10px]","children":["$","$L3",null,{"src":"/images/baja/baja-front.jpg","alt":"Front-on shot of vehicle with Fox shocks visible on both sides and double A-arm geometry clear","fill":true,"className":"object-cover"}]}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The suspension system is what I own. That means:"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Geometry first. Choosing the suspension architecture, defining kinematic parameters (track width, wheelbase, camber curves, roll center height), and validating the design under SAE rules."}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Then CAD. Modeling every component in Fusion 360, producing drawings that can be fabricated from, iterating based on team review and faculty feedback."}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Then fabrication. Welding components in-house or working with local manufacturers for parts beyond our shop capability."}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The suspension has to survive a four-hour endurance race on rough terrain. Getting the geometry right is critical to ensure our car passes the finish line."}],["$","div",null,{"className":"grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"relative aspect-[4/3] overflow-hidden rounded-[10px]","children":["$","$L3",null,{"src":"/images/baja/baja-overhead.jpg","alt":"Overhead angle of vehicle with Miller welder in foreground and engine and drivetrain visible","fill":true,"className":"object-cover"}]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"relative aspect-[4/3] overflow-hidden rounded-[10px]","children":["$","$L3",null,{"src":"/images/baja/baja-team.jpg","alt":"Team member working on suspension area from above","fill":true,"className":"object-cover"}]}]]}]]}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"mb-16","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"mb-4 text-[20px] font-semibold text-primary","children":"Where we are"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"space-y-6 text-[15px] leading-[1.75] text-secondary","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"relative aspect-[4/3] w-full overflow-hidden rounded-[10px]","children":["$","$L3",null,{"src":"/images/baja/baja-side.jpg","alt":"Side profile of vehicle with engine mounted, wheels on, seat visible, and welder next to it","fill":true,"className":"object-cover"}]}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Here is the most recent picture of our car. The drivetrain is in, the suspenson is fully mounted, the seat is in, and we can roll it around the shop. We even have a seat! Rolling it around the shop was a huge milestone for us."}],["$","p",null,{"children":"There is still a lot to do: install the footbox and breaks, electronics, body panels... But we have a functioning chassis and suspension, which is the critical path for the rest of the project. We can start testing subsystems and iterating on our design based on feedback from test drives."}]]}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"mb-16 rounded-[10px] px-5 py-4","style":{"border":"0.5px solid #e0ddd4"},"children":[["$","p",null,{"className":"font-mono text-[12px] font-medium text-amber-600","children":"In Progress"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"mt-1 text-[14px] leading-[1.7] text-secondary","children":"This project is ongoing. This page will be updated as we approach competition."}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"border-t border-border pt-8","children":["$","$L2",null,{"href":"/projects/reaction-time-pcb","className":"text-[13px] font-medium text-accent transition-opacity hover:opacity-80","children":"Next project: Custom PCB →"}]}]]}]}],null],null],null]},[null,["$","$L4",null,{"parallelRouterKey":"children","segmentPath":["children","projects","children","$5","children"],"error":"$undefined","errorStyles":"$undefined","errorScripts":"$undefined","template":["$","$L6",null,{}],"templateStyles":"$undefined","templateScripts":"$undefined","notFound":"$undefined","notFoundStyles":"$undefined"}]],null]},[null,["$","$L4",null,{"parallelRouterKey":"children","segmentPath":["children","projects","children"],"error":"$undefined","errorStyles":"$undefined","errorScripts":"$undefined","template":["$","$L6",null,{}],"templateStyles":"$undefined","templateScripts":"$undefined","notFound":"$undefined","notFoundStyles":"$undefined"}]],null]},[[[["$","link","0",{"rel":"stylesheet","href":"/_next/static/css/850ad522cbe0d2c4.css","precedence":"next","crossOrigin":"$undefined"}]],["$","html",null,{"lang":"en","className":"__variable_37ef13 __variable_6d24ac","style":{"backgroundColor":"#f7f6f2"},"children":["$","body",null,{"className":"font-sans antialiased","children":[["$","$L7",null,{}],["$","$L4",null,{"parallelRouterKey":"children","segmentPath":["children"],"error":"$undefined","errorStyles":"$undefined","errorScripts":"$undefined","template":["$","$L6",null,{}],"templateStyles":"$undefined","templateScripts":"$undefined","notFound":[["$","title",null,{"children":"404: This page could not be found."}],["$","div",null,{"style":{"f